#######################################################################################################################################
Task: The system admins team of xFusionCorp Industries needs to deploy a new application on App Server 1 in Stratos Datacenter. 
They have some pre-requites to get ready that server for application deployment. Prepare the server as per requirements shared below:


1. Install and configure nginx on App Server 1.


2. On App Server 1 there is a self signed SSL certificate and key present at location /tmp/nautilus.crt and /tmp/nautilus.key. 
Move them to some appropriate location and deploy the same in Nginx.


3. Create an index.html file with content Welcome! under Nginx document root.


4. For final testing try to access the App Server 1 link (either hostname or IP) from jump host using curl command.
For example curl -Ik https://<app-server-ip>/.

#######################################################################################################################################
Soltion:
1Ô∏è‚É£ Install and start Nginx
sudo yum install -y nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx
Verify:
systemctl status nginx

2Ô∏è‚É£ Move SSL certificate and key to proper location
sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl
Move the files:
sudo mv /tmp/nautilus.crt /etc/nginx/ssl/
sudo mv /tmp/nautilus.key /etc/nginx/ssl/
Set proper permissions:
sudo chmod 600 /etc/nginx/ssl/nautilus.key
sudo chmod 644 /etc/nginx/ssl/nautilus.crt

3Ô∏è‚É£ Configure Nginx to use SSL
sudo vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

Inside the http { ... } block, add or modify a server block like this:

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name _;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/ssl/nautilus.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/nautilus.key;

    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}


Test configuration:
sudo nginx -t
Restart Nginx:
sudo systemctl restart nginx
4Ô∏è‚É£ Create index.html
echo "Welcome!" | sudo tee /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html


Verify:

cat /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

5Ô∏è‚É£ Test from Jump Host

From the jump host, run:

curl -Ik https://<app-server-1-ip>/


Expected output should include:

HTTP/1.1 200 OK


and SSL details (self-signed warnings are normal).

‚úî Nginx installed and running
‚úî SSL deployed
‚úî index.html created
‚úî HTTPS accessible from jump host

Your App Server 1 is now ready for deployment. üöÄ
